 <LiquidCrystal.h> 
 
LiquidCrystal lcd(12, 11, 5, 4, 3, 2); 
 
String messaggi[] = { 
  "Hello world", 
  "Ciao mondo", 
  "Hola mundo", 
  "Hallo Welt", 
  "Bonjour le monde" 
}; 
 
void setup(){ 
  lcd.begin(16, 2); 
} 
 
void loop(){ 
  for(int i = 0; i < 5; i++){ 
    lcd.clear(); 
    lcd.setCursor(0, 0); 
    lcd.print("Tutorial Arduino"); 
    lcd.setCursor(0, 1); 
    lcd.print(messaggi[i]); 
    delay(1000); 
  } 
}

import socket
import sys
import pygame as pg
import time as t
from _thread import *

__host = "
"
__port = "8585"
__connection = True
__accept = True
__run = True

class Functions():
        
        def play(sample, duration=0):
                file_name = "./samples/" + sample + ".wav"
                s = pg.mixer.Sound(file_name)
                if(duration == 0):
                        
()
                else:
                        
()
                        t.sleep(duration/1000)
                        s.stop()
                

        
def PyGameInit():
        pg.mixer.pre_init(44100, 16, 2, 4096)
        pg.mixer.init()

        
class Socket():

        global __host
        
        def setup():
                global __host
                
                s = socket.socket(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_STREAM)
        
                try:
                        s.bind((__host, __port))
                        
                except socket.error as e:
                        print(str(e))

                s.listen(5)

        def client(connection):
                connection.send(str.encode('Type Your Info\n'))

                while __connection:
                        
                        data = connection.recv(2048)
                        
                        reply = "Server Output: " + data.decode('utf-8') 
                        if not data:
                                break

                        connection.sendall(str.encode(reply))

                connection.close()

        def accept():
                while __accept:
                        connection, address = s.accept()
                        print("Connected to: " + address[0] + ":" + str(address[1]))

                        start_new_thread(Socket.client, (connection,))
                        
def main():
        PyGameInit()
        Socket.setup()
        Socket.accept()
        

if __run:
        main()

Un ciclo di clock a 3000 (1500 MHz di frequenza reale) √® pi√π veloce di un ciclo di clock a 2133 (1066 MHz reali). Esistono alcune formule che traducono i parametri di latenza in nanosecondi, cio√® in un valore direttamente confrontabile. Un ciclo di clock di un modulo ddr4 2133 √® pari a 0,9375 ns (nanosecondi), un ciclo di un modulo ddr4 3000 √® pari a 0,667 ns. Il parametro CAS Latency (CL) del modulo 2133 √® 15, cio√® √® pari a 15 x 0,9375 = 14,0675 ns; il CL del modulo 3000 √® 16, cio√® √® pari a 16 x 0,667 = 10,667 ns.  tempo 100

int a;
long time;

void setup() {
  pinMode(6,INPUT);
  pinMode(5,OUTPUT);
  Serial.begin(9600);
}

void loop() {
  a=0;
  if(digitalRead(6)){
    Serial.println("PRIMO");
    delay(tempo);
    time=millis();
    a=1;
    while(millis()-time<200){
      if(digitalRead(6)){
        a=0;
        break;
      }
    }
    if(a){
      Serial.println("SECONDO");
      delay(tempo);
      a=0;
      time=millis();
      while(millis()-time<200){
        if(digitalRead(6)){
          a=1;
          break;
        }
      }
      if(a){
        Serial.println("TERZO");
        delay(tempo);
        time=millis();
        a=1;
        while(millis()-time<200){
          if(digitalRead(6)){
            a=0;
            break;
          }
        }
        if(a){
          Serial.println("OTTIMO\n\n\n");
          esegui();
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

void esegui(){
  digitalWrite(5,!digitalRead(5));
  delay(1000);
}
